---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About — Metronome News"
	description="About Metronome News — crypto and Web3 journalism with a steady beat. Independent, ad-free, reader-funded."
>
	<main class="static-page container">
		<header class="page-header">
			<div class="page-badge">About</div>
			<h1>Metronome News</h1>
			<p class="page-tagline">Crypto & Web3 journalism with a steady beat.</p>
		</header>

		<div class="prose">
			<p class="lead">
				Metronome News is an independent publication covering cryptocurrency, blockchain,
				and the broader Web3 ecosystem. We aim to cut through the noise with clear,
				thoughtful coverage that respects your time.
			</p>

			<h2>Why Metronome?</h2>
			<p>
				The crypto news cycle is deafening. Every hour brings new tokens, new protocols,
				new narratives. Most of it is noise — paid promotion, copypasted press releases,
				hot takes without substance.
			</p>
			<p>
				We think crypto deserves better. A metronome keeps rhythm steady regardless of
				the tempo around it. That's the posture we want to bring to crypto coverage:
				measured, consistent, clear.
			</p>

			<h2>What we cover</h2>
			<p>We focus on eight core areas:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Bitcoin</strong> — ETF flows, on-chain data, macro narratives</li>
				<li><strong>Ethereum</strong> — upgrades, L2 ecosystem, DeFi on mainnet</li>
				<li><strong>Altcoins</strong> — everything beyond BTC and ETH that matters</li>
				<li><strong>DeFi</strong> — protocols, yield, risks, and the innovation cycle</li>
				<li><strong>NFTs</strong> — past the hype, into real use cases</li>
				<li><strong>Regulation</strong> — what lawmakers do and how it affects you</li>
				<li><strong>Market Analysis</strong> — data over opinion</li>
				<li><strong>Web3</strong> — the broader decentralized stack</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Our principles</h2>
			<p>Three rules we try to keep:</p>
			<ol>
				<li><strong>No shilling.</strong> We don't take payment to cover projects.</li>
				<li><strong>Sources over speculation.</strong> Every claim links to its origin.</li>
				<li><strong>Respect your time.</strong> Short when possible, long only when needed.</li>
			</ol>

			<h2>Who's behind this</h2>
			<p>
				Metronome News is a one-person operation (for now). I'm <strong>raptor</strong>,
				an independent writer covering crypto and Web3. If you'd like to collaborate,
				suggest a story, or just say hi —
				<a href="/contact">get in touch</a>.
			</p>

			<h2>How to support</h2>
			<p>
				The best way to support Metronome News is to read the articles, share the ones
				you find useful, and tell one person who also reads too much crypto news.
				We don't run ads on readers (currently) and don't take sponsored content.
			</p>

			<h2>Technology</h2>
			<p>
				This site is built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro</a>,
				hosted on GitHub Pages, and written in Markdown. No trackers, no ads, no
				third-party scripts following you around. The source code is public and open.
			</p>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.static-page {
		max-width: 780px;
		padding-block: 2.5rem 5rem;
	}

	.page-header {
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}
	.page-badge {
		display: inline-block;
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--color-accent);
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
	}
	.page-header h1 {
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		font-weight: 800;
	}
	.page-tagline {
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.prose {
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		line-height: 1.75;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}
	.prose .lead {
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: var(--color-text);
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
		font-weight: 500;
	}
	.prose h2 {
		font-size: 1.55rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		margin-top: 2.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		color: var(--color-text);
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
	}
	.prose p {
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
	}
	.prose ul,
	.prose ol {
		margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
	}
	.prose li {
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}
	.prose a {
		color: var(--color-accent);
		text-decoration: underline;
		text-underline-offset: 3px;
	}
	.prose a:hover {
		color: var(--color-accent-warm);
	}
	.prose strong {
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}
</style>